DB programming with PL/SQL :- 
---------------------------------------------

=> To work with db from pl/sql  execute sql commands from pl/sql program
=> The following commands are be executed from pl/sql program
 
   1  DML  (insert,update,delete,merge,insert all)
   2  DRL  (select)
   3  TCL  (commit,rollback,savepoint)

 SELECT stmt syntax :- 
 ==================

 SELECT  col1,col2,----  INTO  var1,var2
 FROM tabname
 [ WHERE cond] ; 

 Ex :- 

 SELECT  ename,sal  INTO  n,s
 FROM emp 
 WHERE empno = 7844;

 => wap to input empno and print name & salary ?

   DECLARE
       vempno        NUMBER(4);
       vename        VARCHAR2(10);
       vsal              NUMBER(7,2);
  BEGIN
        vempno :=  &empno ;      
        SELECT ename,sal INTO vename,vsal FROM emp WHERE empno = vempno;
        DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE(vename||'   '||vsal);
  END;
     /

